    "body": "### Problem\n\nCertain keys in neovim will be repeated on key release when using the foot terminal emulator. This is seemingly present in all modes.\n\nKeys I have found to have this incorrect behaviour are the directional arrow keys, enter, tab, and backspace. From what I understand, these key events all use escape sequences, so I suspect the issue is related to how certain events are handled/interpreted with the foot terminal.\n\nI could not reproduce the bug with kitty 0.38.1.\n\nBy using `git bisect`, I have determined that this bug was introduced in commit https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/4fb3b57.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Checkout commit https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/4fb3b57 or later.\n2. $ `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release && make install`\n3. $ `nvim --clean`\n4. Try using the previously mentioned keys.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect keys events to only be registered once per key input instead of both on press and on release.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1505+g822313e42b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.1.984\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora Linux 41\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.19.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
